                           <p xml:lang="en">Panel in secondary use, with a Totenmahl relief, an inscription dated to 308 C.E. in honour of Marcus Aurelius Andronicus 
                           (CIRB 1051) and tamga-shaped sign in the bottom right of the front. The top is sawed off, the relief is weathered. </p>
